            </handDesc>
            <decoDesc/>
            <additions>
              <list>
                <item n="1" xml:id="addition1">
                  <ref target="#handNote3"/>
                  <p>The quires have since been incorrectly renumbered with letters only.</p>
                </item>
                <item n="2" xml:id="addition2">
                  <locus from="211" to="211"/>
                  <ref target="#handNote2"/>
                  <p>Fol. 211 is written by a hand of the <date notBefore="0800" notAfter="0900">9th century</date>, and was probably added by the same person who retouched many portions of the older text.</p>
                </item>
                <item n="3" xml:id="addition3">
                  <ref target="#handNote4"/>
                  <p>Other lessons have been noted by different hands on the margins.</p>
                </item>
                <item n="4" xml:id="addition4">
                  <locus from="211a" to="211a"/>
                  <ref target="#handNote2 #a1"/>
                  <p>On fol. 211 a, after the doxology, there stands a note, informing us that the manuscript belonged to the <placeName ref="">convent of S. Mary Deipara</placeName> in the <placeName ref="">desert of Scete</placeName>. </p>
                  <p><quote xml:lang="syr">ܐܝܬܘܗܝ ܐܘܢܓܠܝܘܢ ܗܢܐ ܩܕܝܫܐ .. ܕܕܝܪܐ ܕܣܘܪ̈ܝܝܐ ܕܒܡܕܒܪܐ ܕܒܡܨܪܝܢ ܕܗ̣ܘ ܐܝܬܘܗܝ ܡܕܒܪܐ ܕܐܣܩ̈ܛܝܣ ܕܝܪܐ ܕܝܠܗܘܢ ܐܝܬܝܗ̇ ܥܠ ܫܡܐ ܩܕܝܫܐ ܕܒܬܘܠܬܐ ܝܠܕܬ ܐܠܗܐ ܡܪܝܡ ܕܒܨ̈ܠܘܗ̇ ܩܕܝܫ̈ܬܐ ܢܫܟ݁ܢ ܠܢ ܪ̈ܚܡܐ ܘܚܢܢܐ ܒܝܘܡܐ ܕܡܬܓܠܝܢܘܬܗ ܫܒܝܚܬܐ ܕܡܫܝܚܐ ܐܠܗܐ ܣܒܪܐ ܕܟܪ̈ܣܛܝܢܐ. ܏ܘܫ</quote></p>
                </item>
                </list>
              </additions>
